{"title_page": "Hardianto", "text_new": "{{Infobox badminton player\n| name                    = Hardianto\n| image                   =\n| image_size              = \n| caption                 = \n| birth_name              = \n| birth_date              = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1993|2|28}}\n| birth_place             = [[Cilacap Regency]], [[Central Java]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Kisah Dua Pebulu Tangkis Pelatnas Asal Jabar Berbalut Bendera Jateng |url=http://www.jawapos.com/read/2016/09/23/52906/kisah-dua-pebulu-tangkis-pelatnas-asal-jabar-berbalut-bendera-jateng/3 |publisher=[[Jawa Pos Group|Jawa Pos]] |accessdate=9 December 2016|language= Indonesian}}</ref>\n| residence               = \n| height                  = 1.79 m\n| weight                  = \n| country                 = {{INA}}\n| years_active            = \n| handedness              = Right\n| coach                   =\n| event                   = Men's doubles\n| highest_ranking         = 14 MD with [[Berry Angriawan]]\n| date_of_highest_ranking = 18 January 2018\n| current_ranking         = 35 MD with [[Berry Angriawan]]\n| date_of_current_ranking = 10 September 2019\n| medal_templates         =\n{{MedalSport | Men's [[badminton]] }}\n{{MedalCountry | {{INA}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition | [[Badminton at the Southeast Asian Games|Southeast Asian Games]] }}\n{{MedalGold | [[Badminton at the 2017 Southeast Asian Games|2017 Kuala Lumpur]] | [[Badminton at the 2017 Southeast Asian Games \u2013 Men's team|Men's team]] }}\n| bwf_id                  = 457FD1A8-5F55-4158-BD1C-CCAF8C8667BE\n}}\n\n'''Hardianto''' (born 28 February 1993) is an [[Indonesia]]n [[badminton]] player from Mutiara Cardinal Bandung club.<ref>{{cite web|title=Players: Hardianto Hardianto |url=http://bwfbadminton.com/player/69003/hardianto-hardianto|publisher=[[Badminton World Federation]]|accessdate=9 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Pemain: Hardianto |url=https://badmintonindonesia.org/app/profile/timnas.aspx?id=000009684 |publisher=[[Badminton Association of Indonesia]] |accessdate=9 December 2016|language= Indonesian}}</ref>\n\n==Achievements==\n\n=== BWF World Tour (1 title, 1 runner-up) ===\nThe BWF World Tour, announced on 19 March 2017 and implemented in 2018,<ref>{{cite news|title=BWF Launches New Events Structure|url=http://bwfbadminton.com/news-single/2017/03/19/bwf-launches-new-event-structure/|publisher=[[Badminton World Federation]]|date=29 November 2017}}</ref> is a series of elite badminton tournaments, sanctioned by [[Badminton World Federation]] (BWF). The BWF World Tour are divided into six levels, namely World Tour Finals, Super 1000, Super 750, Super 500, Super 300 (part of the HSBC World Tour), and the BWF Tour Super 100.<ref>{{cite news|title=Action-Packed Season Ahead!|url=http://bwfworldtour.com/news-single/2018/01/10/action-packed-season-ahead/|publisher=[[Badminton World Federation]]|date=15 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n''Men's doubles''\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 90%;\"\n! Year\n! Tournament\n! Level\n! Partner\n! Opponent\n! Score\n! Result\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | [[2018 Australian Open (badminton)#Finals 3|2018]] \n| align=\"left\" | [[Australian Open (badminton)|Australian Open]] <sup>(1)</sup> \n| align=\"left\" | Super 300 \n| align=\"left\" | {{flagicon|INA}} [[Berry Angriawan]]\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagicon|INA}} [[Wahyu Nayaka]] <br /> {{flagicon|INA}} [[Ade Yusuf]]  \n| align=\"left\" | 21\u20139, 9\u201321, 21\u201315\n| style=\"text-align:left; background:white\" | {{gold1}} '''Champion'''\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | [[2018 New Zealand Open (badminton)#Finals 3|2018]] \n| align=\"left\" | [[New Zealand Open (badminton)|New Zealand Open]] \n| align=\"left\" | Super 300 \n| align=\"left\" | {{flagicon|INA}} [[Berry Angriawan]]\n| align=\"left\" | {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Chen Hung-ling]] <br /> {{flagicon|TPE}} [[Wang Chi-lin]] \n| align=\"left\" | 17\u201321, 17\u201321\n| style=\"text-align:left; background:white\" | {{silver2}} '''Runner-up'''\n|}\n\n=== BWF Grand Prix (2 titles, 0 runner-up) ===\nThe BWF Grand Prix has two level such as [[BWF Grand Prix and Grand Prix Gold|Grand Prix and Grand Prix Gold]]. It is a series of badminton tournaments, sanctioned by [[Badminton World Federation]] (BWF) since 2007.\n\n''Men's doubles''\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 90%;\"\n! Year\n! Tournament\n! Partner\n! Opponent\n! Score\n! Result\n|- style=\"background:#FFD700\"\n| align=\"center\"|[[2017 Thailand Open Grand Prix Gold#Men.27s_Doubles|2017]]\n| align=\"left\"|[[Thailand Open (badminton)|Thailand Open]] <sup>(1)</sup>\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|INA}} [[Berry Angriawan]]\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|GER}} [[Raphael Beck (badminton)|Raphael Beck]] <br />{{flagicon|GER}} [[Peter Kaesbauer]]\n| align=\"left\"|21\u201316, 21\u201316\n| style=\"text-align:left; background:white\"|{{gold1}} '''Champion'''\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#FFD700\"\n| align=\"center\"|[[2017 Malaysia Masters Grand Prix Gold#Men.27s Doubles|2017]]\n| align=\"left\"|[[Malaysia Masters]] <sup>(1)</sup>\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|INA}} [[Berry Angriawan]]\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|MAS}} [[Goh Sze Fei]] <br> {{flagicon|MAS}} [[Nur Izzuddin Mohd Rumsani]]\n| align=\"left\"|21\u201319, 21\u201312\n| style=\"text-align:left; background:white\"|{{gold1}} '''Champion'''\n|}\n:{{Color box|#FFD700|border=darkgray}} [[BWF Grand Prix Gold and Grand Prix|BWF Grand Prix Gold]] tournament\n:{{Color box|#D4F1C5|border=darkgray}} [[BWF Grand Prix Gold and Grand Prix|BWF Grand Prix]] tournament\n\n=== BWF International Challenge/Series (2 titles, 2 runners-up) ===\n''Men's doubles''\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 90%;\"\n! Year\n! Tournament\n! Partner\n! Opponent\n! Score\n! Result\n|-\n|- style=\"background:#D8CEF6\"\n| align=\"center\"|2016\n| align=\"left\"|[[Orleans International]]\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|INA}} [[Kenas Adi Haryanto]]\n| align=\"left\"|{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Richard Eidestedt]]<br>