]]''\n| Big Al\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2016\n| ''[[The Land Before Time: Journey of the Brave]]''\n| Grandpa Longneck\n| Voice role<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/from-universal-pictures-home-entertainment-the-land-before-time-journey-of-the-brave-300194315.html |title=From Universal Pictures Home Entertainment: The Land Before Time: Journey of the Brave |date=December 17, 2015 |accessdate=February 1, 2016 |publisher=PR Newswire |author=Universal Pictures Home Entertainment}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Range 15]]''\n| President\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Three Days in August]]''\n| John\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Bigger Fatter Liar]]''\n| Larry Wolf\n| Direct-to-video<ref>{{cite press release |url=http://www.kusi.com/story/34454732/from-universal-pictures-home-entertainment-ricky-garcia-and-barry-bostwick-go-head-to-head-in-the-all-new-side-splitting-comedy-bigger-fatter-liar |title=From Universal Pictures Home Entertainment: Ricky Garcia And Barry Bostwick Go Head To Head In The All-New Side-Splitting Comedy Bigger Fatter Liar |publisher=Universal Pictures Home Entertainment |via=[[KUSI]] |date=February 8, 2017 |access-date=February 9, 2017 |url-status = dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170211075230/http://www.kusi.com/story/34454732/from-universal-pictures-home-entertainment-ricky-garcia-and-barry-bostwick-go-head-to-head-in-the-all-new-side-splitting-comedy-bigger-fatter-liar |archivedate=February 11, 2017 |df= }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2018\n| ''[[Incredibles 2]]''\n| Mayor\n| Voice role<ref>{{cite press release |url=https://variety.com/2018/film/reviews/incredibles-2-review-holly-hunter-1202837069/r |title=Film Review: \u2018Incredibles 2\u2019 |publisher=Variety |date=June 11, 2018 |access-date=June 13, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''Santa Girl''\n| Santa Claus\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2019\n| ''Grand-Daddy Day Care''\n| Dynamite Dan North\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Undercover Brother 2]]''\n| The Man\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[American Pie Presents: Girls' Rules]]''\n| PeePaw\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 1979\n| ''[[Murder by Natural Causes]]''\n| Gil Weston\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1979\n| ''[[You Can't Take It with You (play)#Film and TV adaptations|You Can't Take It With You]]''\n| Anthony Kirby, Jr.\n| Television film (note: filmed version of the play)\n|-\n| 1979\n| ''[[Hawaii Five-O (1968 TV series)|Hawaii Five-O]]''\n| Lucas Sandover\n| Episode \"Year of the Horse\"\n|-\n| 1980\n| ''[[Scruples (miniseries)|Scruples]]''\n| Spider Elliot\n| Television miniseries\n|-\n| 1981\n| ''Red Flag: The Ultimate Game''\n| Maj. Jay Rivers\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1982\n| ''[[Working (musical)|Working]]'' \n| Steelworker\n| [[American Playhouse]] production\n|-\n| 1983 \n| ''Summer Girl''\n| Gavin Shelburne\n| Television film \n|-\n| 1983\n| ''An Uncommon Love'' \n| Mr. Kinser\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1984\n| ''[[George Washington (miniseries)|George Washington]]'' \n| Gen. [[George Washington]]\n| Television miniseries\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''[[A Woman of Substance (miniseries)|A Woman of Substance]]''\n| Major Paul McGill\n| Television miniseries\n|-\n| 1985\n| ''Deceptions''\n| Grant Roberts\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1986\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | ''[[George Washington II: The Forging of a Nation]]''\n| President [[George Washington]]\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1986\n| ''Betrayed By Innocence''\n| Nick DeLeon \n| Television film\n|-\n| 1987 \n| ''[[I'll Take Manhattan (miniseries)|I'll Take Manhattan]]''\n| Zachary Amberville\n| Television miniseries\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''[[War and Remembrance (miniseries)|War and Remembrance]]''\n| style=\"white-space:nowrap;\" | Lieutenant Carter \"Lady\" Aster \n| Television miniseries\n|-\n| 1988\n| ''[[Body of Evidence (1988 film)|Body of Evidence]]''\n| Mark Dwyer\n| Television film\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[[Judith Krantz's Till We Meet Again|Till We Meet Again]]''\n| Terrence 'Mac' McGuire\n| Television miniseries\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''[