{"title_page": "Katha (2009 film)", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=October 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Katha\n| image =\n| alt = <!-- see WP:ALT -->\n| caption =\n| director = Srinivas Raga\n| producer = Urmila Gunnam\n| writer = [[Gangaraju Gunnam]]\n| screenplay =\n| story =\n| starring =[[Genelia D'Souza]]<br> [[Adith Arun]]<br>[[Prakash Raj]] <br>[[Aamir Tameem]]\n| music = S. K. Balachandran\n| studio = Just Yellow Media\n| distributor = Just Yellow Media\n| released = {{Film date|df=yes|2009|12|12}}\n| country = India\n| language = Telugu\n| budget =\n| gross =\n}}\n\n'''''Katha''''' is a 2009 [[Telugu language|Telugu]]-language thriller film directed by Srinivas Raga. The film stars [[Genelia D'Souza]] in the lead and is produced by Urmila Gunnam.<ref>[http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-katha.html Katha film review \u2013 Telugu cinema Review \u2013 Genelia & Arun]. Idlebrain.com (12 December 2009).</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nChitra ([[Genelia]]) is a loner who comes to [[Araku]] seeking employment as a school teacher. Krishna (Arun) is an aspiring director who comes to Araku for a test shoot and to complete the script of his debut film. Circle Inspector ([[Prakash Raj]]) has a wife and young kids. Chitra spent a year in a mental asylum because she witnessed her family being murdered. Chitra and Krishna become friends. While Chitra is looking through her binoculars, she witnesses a murder where she can clearly see the victim's face. Chitra reports the incident to the police, but they find no evidence of the crime. Chitra suspects that her past mental condition is relapsing. Eventually, the police finds out that the female victim did, in fact, exist. They have a CD that shows Circle Inspector and the female victim together in a store. The victim is none other than the Circle Inspector's dead girlfriend's daughter. He cannot acknowledge their illegitimate relation without tainting his reputation. It is revealed that he lured his daughter to Araku to kill her. Although Chitra witnessed the murder, the Circle Inspector tried to make it look like a figment of Chitra's imagination, and is infuriated when Chitra refuses to believe that the murder was her hallucination. Chitra and Krishna try to take the disc and escape, but Circle Inspector tries to kill Krishna, whose foot is injured by Krishna. Circle Inspector's holds Krishna at gunpoint, but Chitra refuses to give the disc to him. She slaps the Circle Inspector, who decides to let go of Krishna and commits suicide. Chitra says that she didn't think that Circle Inspector was going to kill her and Krishna because he already framed a dead officer for the victim's murder. Chitra and Krishna take the disc as evidence to the police. The film ends with the union of Chitra and Krishna.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Genelia D'Souza]] as Chitra Singh\n* [[Adith Arun]] as Krishna\n* [[Prakash Raj]]\n* [[Aamir Tameem]] as Raghu\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Katha\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = S.K.Balachadran\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 2009\n| genre        = Feature film soundtrack\n| length       = 19:54\n| language     = Telugu\n| label        = Vel Records\n| producer     = \n| prev_title   = \n| prev_year    = \n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n}}\n<br />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2009 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2000s Telugu-language films]]\n\n\n{{2000s-Telugu-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=October 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name = Katha\n| image =\n| alt = <!-- see WP:ALT -->\n| caption =\n| director = Srinivas Raga\n| producer = Urmila Gunnam\n| writer = [[Gangaraju Gunnam]]\n| screenplay =\n| story =\n| starring =[[Genelia D'Souza]]<br> [[Adith Arun]]<br>[[Prakash Raj]] <br>[[Aamir Tameem]]\n| music = S. K. Balachandran\n| studio = Just Yellow Media\n| distributor = Just Yellow Media\n| released = {{Film date|df=yes|2009|12|12}}\n| country = India\n| language = Telugu\n| budget =\n| gross =\n}}\n\n'''''Katha''''' is a 2009 [[Telugu language|Telugu]]-language thriller film directed by Srinivas Raga. The film stars [[Genelia D'Souza]] in the lead and is produced by Urmila Gunnam.<ref>[http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-katha.html Katha film review \u2013 Telugu cinema Review \u2013 Genelia & Arun]. Idlebrain.com (12 December 2009).</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nChitra ([[Genelia]]) is a loner who comes to [[Araku]] seeking employment as a school teacher. Krishna (Arun) is an aspiring director who comes to Araku for a test shoot and to complete the script of his debut film. Circle Inspector ([[Prakash Raj]]) has a wife and young kids. Chitra spent a year in a mental asylum because she witnessed her family being murdered. Chitra and Krishna become friends. While Chitra is looking through her binoculars, she witnesses a murder where she can clearly see the victim's face. Chitra reports the incident to the police, but they find no evidence of the crime. Chitra suspects that her past mental condition is relapsing. Eventually, the police finds out that the female victim did, in fact, exist. They have a CD that shows Circle Inspector and the female victim together in a store. The victim is none other than the Circle Inspector's dead girlfriend's daughter. He cannot acknowledge their illegitimate relation without tainting his reputation. It is revealed that he lured his daughter to Araku to kill her. Although Chitra witnessed the murder, the Circle Inspector tried to make it look like a figment of Chitra's imagination, and is infuriated when Chitra refuses to believe that the murder was her hallucination. Chitra and Krishna try to take the disc and escape, but Circle Inspector tries to kill Krishna, whose foot is injured by Krishna. Circle Inspector's holds Krishna at gunpoint, but Chitra refuses to give the disc to him. She slaps the Circle Inspector, who decides to let go of Krishna and commits suicide. Chitra says that she didn't think that Circle Inspector was going to kill her and Krishna because he already framed a dead officer for the victim's murder. Chitra and Krishna take the disc as evidence to the police. The film ends with the union of Chitra and Krishna.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[Genelia D'Souza]] as Chitra Singh\n* [[Adith Arun]] as Krishna\n* [[Prakash Raj]]\n* [[Aamir Tameem]] as Raghu\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Soundtrack album by S.K.Balachandran\n| type         = \n| artist       = \n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 2009\n| genre        = Feature film soundtrack\n| length       = 19:54\n| label        = Vel Records\n| producer     = \n| prev_title   = \n| prev_year    = \n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n}}\n<br />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2009 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2000s Telugu-language films]]\n\n\n{{2000s-Telugu-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "JohnsonKumar", "label": "safe", "comment": "Corrected and added Language of the soundtrack", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Katha_(2009_film)"}
{"title_page": "Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa", "text_new": "{{short description|2010 film by Gautham Menon}}\n{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya\n| image          = Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Gautham Menon]]\n| producer       = [[Escape Artists Motion Pictures|P. Madan]]<br />[[VTV Ganesh]]<br />[[Elred Kumar]]<br />Jayaraman\n| writer         = [[Gautham Menon]]\n| starring       = [[Silambarasan]]<br />[[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]]\n| narrator       = [[Silambarasan]]\n| music          = [[A. R. Rahman]]\n| cinematography = [[Manoj Paramahamsa]]\n| editing        = [[Anthony (film editor)|Anthony Gonsalves]]\n| studio         = [[Escape Artists Motion Pictures]]<br />[[RS Infotainment]]\n| distributor    = [[Udhayanidhi Stalin|Red Giant Movies]]<br/>Two95 Entertainment\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2010|02|26}}\n| runtime        = 167 minutes\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = Tamil\n}}\n'''''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa''''' ({{Literal translation|Will you cross the skies for me?}}) is a 2010 Indian Tamil-language [[romantic drama]] film directed and written by [[Gautham Menon]], featuring [[Silambarasan]] and [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]] in the lead roles. The film, distributed by [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]], features [[Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] composed by [[A. R. Rahman]], cinematography by [[Manoj Paramahamsa]] and editing by [[Anthony (film editor)|Anthony Gonsalves]]. The story was simultaneously shot in [[Cinema of Andhra Pradesh|Telugu]] as ''[[Ye Maaya Chesave]]'', starring [[Naga Chaitanya]] and [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu]], however, with a different cast and climax.<ref name=\"remake\">{{cite news|author=Daithota, Madhu|title='I don't treat Naga Chaitanya like a star kid'|work=Times of India|accessdate=14 September 2009 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/I-dont-treat-Naga-Chaitanya-like-a-star-kid/articleshow/5005397.cms|date=14 September 2009}}</ref>\n\nLaunched after a wave of publicity posters with no details about the cast and crew, ''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'' began its first schedule of filming in February 2009.<ref name=\"mystery\">{{cite web|year=2009|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya \u2013 The Silambarasan mystery unveiled|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=13 February 2009|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-09-02/vinnaithaandi-varuvaaya-13-02-09.html}}</ref> Shooting continued through 2009, with the film garnering significant media interest, through schedules in Malta and the United States.<ref name=\"malta\">{{cite web|author=Moviebuzz|year=2009|title=Simbu and Trisha go to Malta|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=12 May 2009|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14887420}}</ref> Before release, it became the first Tamil project to have a music soundtrack premiere outside of India, with a successful launch at the [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTAs) in London.<ref name=\"abroadmusic\">{{cite web|year=2009|title=Silambarasan, Trisha, Gautam & Rahman in London! |publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=21 December 2009|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/dec-09-04/silambarasan-trisha-vinnaithaandi-varuvaaya-21-12-09.html}}</ref>\n\n''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'' explores the complicated relationship between a [[Hindu]] [[Tamils|Tamil]] boy, Karthik Sivakumar, and a [[Malayali]] [[Christianity|Christian]] girl, Jessie Thekekuttu from [[Alappuzha]], [[Kerala]]. Karthik falls in love with Jessie only to be met by her indifference and reluctance as they belong to different religions and her strict conservative family will never consent to their union. The film released on 26 February 2010, along with the Telugu version to advance bookings worldwide.<ref name=\"rediff1\">{{cite web|publisher=[[Rediff]]|url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/jun/23/slide-show-1-south-half-year-report-of-tamil-cinema.htm|title=Half-yearly BO report: Suriya rules Tamil|date=23 June 2010|accessdate=23 June 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"behindwoods.com\">{{citation|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-slide-shows/movie-4/box-office-2010/vinnaithaandi-varuvaayaa.html|title=Box Office 2010|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref> Upon release, it achieved highly positive reviews, with several critics giving \"modern classic\" status, whilst also becoming a commercially successful venture.<ref name=\"rediffreview\">{{cite web|author=Srinivasan, Pavithra|year=2010|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa is a must watch|publisher=[[Rediff]]|accessdate=26 February 2010|url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/feb/26/review-vinnaithaandi-varuvaayaa.htm}}</ref><ref name=\"sifyreview\">{{cite web|publisher=[[Sify]]|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya review|accessdate=26 February 2010|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=14933091&ctid=5&cid=2429}}</ref> It was later remade in [[Bollywood|Hindi]] as ''[[Ekk Deewana Tha]]'' starring [[Prateik Babbar]] and [[Amy Jackson]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Maybe I got the casting wrong: Gautham Menon|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-02-28/news-interviews/31107562_1_amy-jackson-gautham-menon-ekk-deewana-tha|accessdate=11 May 2012|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=28 February 2012|author=Sunayana Suresh}}</ref> in 2012. After the seven years, [[Gautham Menon]] officially announced, that a filming of a sequel would begin soon with new four actors and Silambarasan.\n\n==Plot==\n\nKarthik ([[Silambarasan]]) is a [[Mechanical Engineering]] graduate in [[Chennai]] who aspires to become a filmmaker. His friend introduces him to cinematographer Ganesh ([[Ganesh Janardhanan]]). With Ganesh's help Karthik becomes an assistant to director [[K. S. Ravikumar]]. Karthik's family, who are [[Tamil people|Tamil]] Hindu's, rent Jessie's ([[Trisha Krishnan]]) house. Jessie is from a conservative [[Malayali people|Malayali]] [[Saint Thomas Christians|Nasrani Christian]]/Syrian Catholic family from [[Alappuzha]], [[Kerala]], that lives upstairs.<ref name=\"manorama\">{{cite web|publisher=[[Malayala Manorama|Metro Manorama Kochi]]|title=Marunadan Cinemayile Malayali|accessdate=1 November 2014|url=http://epaper.manoramaonline.com/edaily/FlashClient/Show_Story_IPad.aspx?storySrc=aHR0cDovL2VwYXBlci5tYW5vcmFtYW9ubGluZS5jb20vTU1EYWlseS9Lb2NoaS8yMDE0LzExLzAxL0YvTU1EYWlseV9Lb2NoaV8yMDE0XzExXzAxX0ZfTVRfMDI2X1BSLmpwZw==&uname=&ipad=N}}</ref> Karthik falls in love with Jessie the moment he meets her. Karthik tries to interact with Jessie, who is afraid of speaking to men around her strict father, and ends up angering her. Unable to hide his feelings any longer, Karthik confesses his love for her; she does not respond. A few days later, Karthik learns from his sister that Jessie has gone to Kerala to visit her grandmother. He and Ganesh end up in Kerala to look for her. After several days, he finds her and apologises. She introduces him to her family in Kerala as her \"classmate\". Jessie denies she has any feelings for him but agrees to be his friend. On the train journey back home, however, the two get close and share a kiss. Karthik is convinced Jessie loves him; the two meet several times and Jessie begins to admit that she also likes Karthik, but wants to refrain from any problems because she knows her father wouldn't give her hand in marriage to a Hindu. Consequently, due to various misunderstandings between Jessie's brother and Karthik, her parents learn of their supposed affair. They fix a match and schedule her wedding. The day arrives and midway through the ceremony, Jessie refuses to marry the groom, displeasing everyone in her family. Karthik, who had, without anyone's knowledge, come to Kerala to witness the wedding is ecstatic and secretly visits Jessie at her home. It is then that Jessie admits she has indeed fallen in love with him. Karthik and Jessie continue to love each other without the knowledge of their parents.\n\nAt this point of time, Karthik goes to [[Goa]] on a 45-day shoot, where he gets rather busy. Meanwhile, the topic of Jessie's marriage comes up again at her home when the guy whom she refused to marry earlier pays them a visit. Panicking, Jessie calls Karthik and tells him that she wants to elope with him. Karthik, since he is travelling through less than ideal places, tells Jessie to stay in Chennai for now, and that soon he would be back and they can discuss. Jessie stops taking Karthik's calls and so he goes back one night to check on Jessie. He comes to know that Jessie has decided to break up, as the relationship is not peaceful due to her parents' disapproval. She says she has agreed to marry a boy of their choice. When Karthik pleads her not to do it, she tells him that a time had come when she was willing to elope, but the moment was gone. She doesn't want Karthik to wait for her too long, as he has his dreams to fulfill. Karthik later comes to know that she is married and settled abroad in UK.\n\nTwo years later, Karthik meets Nandini ([[Samantha Ruth Prabhu]]). She falls in love with him, but is rejected by Karthik by saying that he hasn't yet gotten over Jessie. He then comes up with a script for his first film, which happens to be his very own love story. He calls upon [[Naga Chaitanya|Naga Chaitanya Akkineni]] as the film's protagonist, Nandini as the female lead and Ganesh as the film's cinematographer, and the film is eventually titled ''Jessie''. While shooting for the film in New York, he sees Jessie and she comes to speak with him. She admits that she is not married and is still in love with him, and he too says she is still in his heart. Karthik proposes yet again and they get married the same day. This is actually revealed to be the end scene in Karthik's movie \u2013 which Karthik and Jessie in real life are watching together in the theatre. After it gets over, it is revealed to the audience that Jessie had in fact seen Karthik in New York but had not come forward to meet him. She is married now and hence asks Karthik to move on. She tells Karthik that they cannot lead a life which is full of obstacles and they part, once and for all to lead different lives and different destinies.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Silambarasan|Simbu]] as Karthik Sivakumar, a [[Tamil people|Tamil]] [[Hindu]].<ref name=\"manorama\"/>\n* [[Trisha Krishnan|Trisha]] as Jessie Thekekuttu, a [[Saint Thomas Christians|Syrian Christian]] Syrian Catholic [[Malayali]] girl.<ref name=\"manorama\"/>\n* [[VTV Ganesh]] as Ganesh, a [[cinematographer]]\n* [[Babu Antony]] as Joseph Thekekuttu\n* [[Kitty (actor)|Kitty]] as Sivakumar\n* [[Uma Padmanabhan]] as Mrs. Sivakumar\n* Arjuna as Jerry Thekekuttu\n* [[Lakshmi Ramakrishnan]] as Teresa Thekekuttu\n* Trisha Alex as Karthik's sister\n* [[K. S. Ravikumar]] as a [[Film director|Director]]\n* [[Pradeep Kottayam]] as George, Jessie's uncle in Kerala.\n* [[Janani Iyer]] as an [[assistant director]] to K. S. Ravikumar.\n* [[Lena (actress)|Lena]] as Rita's mother\n* [[Sudheesh]] as Praveen\n* [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu]] in a cameo appearance as the [[actress]] Nandini\n* [[Naga Chaitanya]] in a cameo appearance as himself\n{{colend}}\n\n==Production==\nAfter making a series of action films, Gautham Menon actively chose to make an \"out and out love story\" at the insistence of his close associates, and marked a return to genre for the first time since ''[[Minnale]]'' (2001). Initially titled ''Vennilavae Vennillavae'', he started writing the film as a simple love story which slowly became an intense love story, as the scripting phase progressed. Stating that the film would narrate the romantic tale of two people called Karthik and Jessie over a period of almost three years, he revealed that the film would be \"conversation driven\" and hoped \"everybody will identify with the lead pair\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?cid=2408&id=14932884|title=Welcome to Sify.com|website=www.sify.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> Menon took the script to producer [[Manjula Ghattamaneni]], who asked him to narrate the film to her brother [[Mahesh Babu]] and the movie was a [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Telugu language|Telugu]] bilingual. Menon initially felt that the film would not suit the actor, but later agreed preliminary terms to make it in Telugu titled ''Jessie'' with the actor and have [[A. R. Rahman]] as the music composer, as he was impressed with the story.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/features/Interviews/interview-5/director/gautham-menon-2.html|title=Director Gautham Vasudev Menon - Interview - Behindwoods.com - Vaaranam Aayiram Kakka Kakka Pachaikili Muthucharam Minnale Suriya Kamal Haasan Kamal Hassan images tamil picture gallery images|website=www.behindwoods.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nContinuing from the earlier proposed theme of ''Vennilavae Vennillavae'', Menon later chose to use the second line of the song to title his film as ''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'', after it was suggested by the cinematographer [[Manoj Paramahamsa]].<ref name=\"rediff\">{{cite web|url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2009/mar/02slde1-gautam-menons-vinnaithandi-varuvaya.htm|title=rediff.com: Gautam Menon's new love story|website=specials.rediff.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> Menon discussed a Tamil and Telugu version of the script with several actors including [[Dhanush]] and [[Allu Arjun]] who had wanted changes to be made to the climax, and described being \"one week away\" from starting the project with a debutant actor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-simbu-is-classy-i-m-local-dhanush-tells-gautham-menon-2206388|title='Simbu is classy, I'm local', Dhanush tells Gautham Menon|date=26 April 2016|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2011/02/12/between-reviews-shooting-from-the-lip/|title=Between Reviews: Shooting from the Lip|date=12 February 2011|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/dhanush-chameleon-simbu-has-too-many-distractions-gautham-menon-interview-53004?amp|title=Dhanush is a chameleon, Simbu has too many distractions: Gautham Menon interview|date=17 November 2016|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> But In late January 2009, Menon confirmed that he was in discussions with [[Silambarasan]] and [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]] to portray the lead roles from the script. After finding out that Silambarasan had dates available as a result of the delay in the shoot of [[Vignesh Shivan]]'s ''[[Podaa Podi]]'' (2012), Menon chose to halt the production of his ongoing ''Chennaiyil Oru Mazhaikaalam'' and finalise pre-production work on ''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa''. Menon added that Silambarasan was \"apt for this kind of a film\" and was \"ready to experiment and try something different\" from his usual film roles, prompting him to agree to star in the film.<ref name=\"rediff\"/> As Menon was working with Trisha on ''Chennaiyil Oru Mazhaikaalam'', he chose to use her dates for ''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'' instead.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/exclusive-gautham-to-start-a-quickie-with-simbu-news-tamil-kkfsxQebaiesi.html|title=Exclusive: Gautham to start a quickie with Simbu!|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> To pique interest before the official announcement, the makers released a series of film posters featuring Silambarasan and Trisha inspired from previous classic Tamil films. The team used posters inspired from ''[[Geethanjali (1989 film)|Geethanjali]]'' (1989), ''[[Minsara Kanavu]]'' (1997), ''[[Dil Se]]'' (1998), ''[[Alaipayuthey]]'' (2000) and ''[[Kaakha Kaakha]]'' (2003). Other members of the technical crew included Menon's regular collaborators editor [[Anthony (film editor)|Anthony]], art director [[Rajeevan]], costume designer Nalini Sriram and lyricist [[Thamarai]]. The project was jointly produced by [[Escape Artists Motion Pictures]] and [[RS Infotainment]], with [[Elred Kumar]], [[VTV Ganesh|Ganesh]], Madhan and Jayaraman as producers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-09-03/vinnaithandi-varuvaaya-16-02-09.html|title=A.R. Rahman to compose for Silambarasan's flick - Behindwoods.com - Tamil Movie News - Vinnaithaandi Varuvaya Silambarasan Trisha Gautham Vasudev Menon A.R. Rahman|website=www.behindwoods.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-09-02/vinnaithaandi-varuvaaya-13-02-09.html|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya - The Silambarasan mystery unveiled - Behindwoods.com - Tamil Movies News - Gautham Menon Trisha A.R. Rahman|website=www.behindwoods.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nFor the role of a mentor to Karthik's character, Menon first approached [[Vivek (actor)|Vivek]], but he turned down the opportunity. Later, one of the film's producers, [[VTV Ganesh|Ganesh]], was cast in the role, in what later became his breakthrough film as an actor.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vm8100Ii8Q4|title=\"Those who know me refer to me as Jessie.\" - One Film One Facet - Gautham Menon|last=Film Companion South|date=20 February 2018|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref> Chennai-based model [[Janani Iyer]] was recruited to portray the role of an assistant director who falls in love with Karthik, but the role was later reshot with [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu|Samantha]], who worked as the lead actress of the film's Telugu version. Janani Iyer was subsequently seen in the background of several scenes where Karthik is shown to be a part of a film production team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/did-you-know|title=Did You Know - Movies - Tamil - Entertainment - The Times of India|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> [[Ashwin Kakumanu]] also auditioned for the role of Jessy's brother in the film and was selected, but eventually did not feature after having a clash of dates.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-actors/ashwin-kakumanu/ashwin-kakumanu-interview.html|title=Ashwin Kakumanu Interview|website=www.behindwoods.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8v6O260NDhE|title=How Gautham Menon Explained a Lip-Lock Scene? - What Happened? - Ashwin Explains - US 56|last=BehindwoodsTV|date=13 July 2017|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nScenes were shot in the lakes of [[Alappuzha]] during April 2009 for a month, with the [[houseboat]]s doubling up as caravans.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/malayalam-film-not-now-says-trisha-news-tamil-kkfsjEbcighsi.html|title=Malayalam film? Not now, says Trisha|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn May, the team moved to [[Malta]] to film the song sequences for \"Hosanna\" and \"Omana Penne\", choreographed by Flexy Stu.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/simbu-and-trisha-go-to-malta-news-tamil-kkfrXGhhjdasi.html|title=Simbu and Trisha go to Malta|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> For the particular song sequences in the film, Menon wanted \"churches, water and caves\" and convinced the producers to finance a trip to Malta, and in the process, the team became the first South Indian film to shoot in the country. Scenes were shot in places including [[Valletta]], [[Mdina]], [[Gozo]] and [[Comino]], as well as in lanes, alleys, eight churches and during the time of a village feast. The makers brought along a crew of twenty-six people to Malta, with ten local workers also helping on the production. The shoot lasted ten days and cost approximately \u20ac90,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20090528/local/bollywood-director-discovers-malta.258682|title=Bollywood director discovers Malta|first=Allied Newspapers|last=Ltd|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.com.mt/articles/2009-07-18/news/tamil-film-partly-shot-in-malta-nearing-completion-227946/|title=Tamil Film partly shot in Malta nearing completion - The Malta Independent|website=www.independent.com.mt|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2009, the team flew to the [[United States]] to complete the final filming schedule. Scenes were shot throughout locations in [[Manhattan]] and [[New Jersey]], with particular shots filmed at [[Brooklyn Bridge]], [[Central Park]] and [[Times Square]].\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/simbu-trisha-off-to-new-york-news-tamil-kkfrvXefdaasi.html|title=Simbu & Trisha off to New York|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/oct-09-03/vinnaithandi-varuvaya-16-10-09.html|title=Silambarasan and Trisha celebrating Deepavali in NY - Tamil Movie News - Vinnaithandi Varuvaya - Silambarasan - Gautham Menon - Trisha - Behindwoods.com|website=www.behindwoods.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe film was given a \"U/A\" certificate by the [[Central Board of Film Certification|Indian Film Certification Board]] as they believed \"the love in the film was too intense for a child to understand\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://silverscreen.in/tamil/features/gautham-menon-interview-on-movies-music-romance/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170216081053/https://silverscreen.in/tamil/features/gautham-menon-interview-on-movies-music-romance/|title=Gautham Menon Interview: On Movies, Music & Romance|archivedate=16 February 2017|work=Silverscreen.in|accessdate=16 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Critical reception===\nThe film opened to highly positive reviews from critics. ''[[Oneindia.in]]'' said \"The slow phase of the second half and frequent use of bad words (Chennai Tamil) are major minuses in Gautham's narration. But these are all not preventing one to enjoy the content of true and painful love of the film!\"<ref>{{citation|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/reviews/2010/vinnaithandi-varuvaya-review-270210.html|title=Vinnaithandi Varuvaya \u2013 Review|publisher=oneindia.in|date=27 February 2010|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n''[[Sify]]'' said that it was \"Very good\" further citing \"The film is a must watch for those who cares for cinema of sense and substance. It stresses the fact that Tamil cinema has to break the mould if it aims to grab eyeballs. Gautham Menon has crafted a movie that will stay in our hearts for a long, long time.\"<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vinnaithaandi-varuvaaya-review-review-tamil-14933091.html|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya review|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref> ''Indiaglitz'' stated \"If and only if, you have all the time in the world, and you like the slow romantic genre, you'll enjoy this one.\"<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/review/10901.html|title=innaithandi Varuvaya Movie Review|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=26 February 2010 |accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nPavithra Srinivasan of ''[[Rediff.com]]'' called the film a \"Must watch\" further citing \"The best part about VTV is that it revolves around people, rather than events. It's like putting a camera into the intimate, everyday life of two people and following them on their adventures. The characters go through a whirlwind of emotions, laugh and cry, and take you along with them.\" However, the reviewer points out certain drawbacks in the film citing \"On the minus side, VTV suffers from the same defect as Vaaranam Aayiram: the second half lags in pace. The dialogues and confrontations are repetitive. There's a would-be love-track that seems unnecessary before the story takes off again.\"<ref>{{citation|url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/feb/26/review-vinnaithaandi-varuvaayaa.htm|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa is a must watch|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|date=26 February 2010|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nMalathi Rangarajan from ''[[The Hindu]]'' said \"Twenty two-year old Karthik's true-to-life overtures, reactions and recklessness are just as you would expect from a director of Menon's calibre. It is his authentic depiction of Jessie's confusion that's all the more amazing \u2013 Menon's complete understanding of a woman's psyche bowls you over! So do the young lovers!\"<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2010/03/05/stories/2010030550040200.htm|title=Taste of candyfloss \u2013 Vinnai Thaandi Varuvaaya|work=The Hindu|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref> Aravindan D. I. of ''nowrunning.com'' gave the film three stars out of five and said \"Gautam Vasudev Menon's \"Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya\" is a clean romantic story without any deviation or sub-plots.\"<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/6351/tamil/vinnaithaandi-varuvaayaa/2498/review.htm|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa Review|publisher=nowrunning.com|date=27 February 2010|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n''Chennai Online'' said, ''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'' (VTV) is an excellent effort on the part of Gautam Vasudev Menon in narrating a clean romantic story without any deviation from the plot\" and further cited \"As is Menon\u2019s forte, the dialogues and the execution of scenes are top-notch. The joys of falling of love and the pangs of separation have been portrayed well. The way Simbu nurtures his love for Jesse and the positive but ambiguous reactions from Trisha to his overtures are very nice indeed.\"<ref>{{citation|url=http://chennaionline.com/movies/moviereviews/20101227121207/Movie-Review-Vinnai-Thaandi-Varuvaaya.col|title=Movie Review: Vinnai Thaandi Varuvaaya|publisher=chennaionline.com|date=27 February 2010|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nRaman Nalluswamy Thevar, an Indian author wrote an [[E-book|e-Book]] titled \"One Awesome Girl\"  which narrates the dialogue \"One-way ticket to Heart-break city\" delivered by Simbu. Raman stated that his debut contains his auto-biography and semi-biography which received positive reviews.\n\n===Box office===\n''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'' took a grand opening, grossing around {{INRConvert|9.7|m}} in its first three days in Chennai.<ref>{{citation|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14933568&cid=13525926|title=CBO \u2013 Feb 26 to 28|date=2 March 2010|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref> The film grossed {{INRConvert|157.5|m}} at the Chennai box office in the 12th weekend. It totally grossed {{INRConvert|500|m}} and was officially declared a blockbuster.<ref name=\"behindwoods.com\"/>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{main|Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa (soundtrack)}}\nThe soundtrack was composed by [[A. R. Rahman]]. ''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'' marked the beginning of a collaboration between Rahman, Silambarasan and [[Gautham Menon]].<ref>{{cite news|first=M|last=Suganth|title=2 crore for NEP audio rights!|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-05-10/news-interviews/31642728_1_audio-industry-ilaiyaraaja-audio-rights|accessdate=3 October 2012|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=10 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe world premiere was held at [[BAFTA]] in London on 18 December 2009 and later it was relaunched in [[Chennai]] on 20 January 2010. The album consists of seven tracks.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-south-top-tamil-films-of-2010/20101209.htm |title=Top Tamil films of 2010\n|publisher=[[Rediff]]|accessdate=9 December 2009}}</ref> The audio received good pre-release response and was marked as No. 1 in Asia, in advance bookings.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/Vinnai-Thandi-Varuvaaya-audio-creates-history-imagegallery-kollywood-kbjmXAjfdfd.html|title=Vinnai Thandi Varuvaaya audio creates history!|publisher=[[Sify]]}}</ref> The album was ranked among the best musicals of 2010.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/62922.html|title=REWIND: The Music of 2010|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=7 January 2011|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n; [[Edison Awards (India)|Edison Awards]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kollytalk.com/cinenews/simbu-and-trisha-win-edison-awards-for-excellence-in-cinema/|title=Simbu and Trisha win Edison awards 2011, for Vinnai Thaandi Varuvaaya|date=15 February 2011|accessdate=17 February 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110622073416/http://www.kollytalk.com/cinenews/simbu-and-trisha-win-edison-awards-for-excellence-in-cinema/|archive-date=22 June 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* Best Actor \u2013 [[Silambarasan Rajendar]]\n* Best Actress \u2013 [[Trisha Krishnan]]\n* Best Male Singer \u2013 [[Vijay Prakash]]\n\n; Vikatan Awards<ref>{{cite news|url=http://kollywoodz.com/exclusive-results-of-ananda-vikatan-awards-2010/|title=Exclusive: Results of Ananda Vikatan Awards 2010|publisher=Kollywoodz}}</ref>\n* Best Music Director \u2013 [[A. R. Rahman]]\n* Best Male Singer \u2013 [[Benny Dayal]]\n* Best Female Singer \u2013 [[Shreya Ghoshal]]\n* Best Lyricist \u2013 [[Thamarai]]\n* Best Costume Designer \u2013 Nalini Sriram<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kollywoodz.com/exclusive-results-of-ananda-vikatan-awards-2010/ |title=Exclusive: Results of Ananda Vikatan Awards 2010 |publisher=Kollywoodz.com |date=22 January 2011 |accessdate=17 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n;BIG Tamil Entertainment Awards<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-08/big-awards-28-03-11.html|title=A 'big' night for Tamil entertainment industry|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n* Most Entertaining Actor \u2013 Silambarasan Rajendar\n* Most Entertaining Male Singer \u2013 Vijay Prakash\n\n; [[Vijay Music Awards]]\n\n* ''Vijay Music awards'' \u2013 A. R. Rahman\n* ''Vijay Music awards'' \u2013 Vijay Prakash\n* ''Vijay Music awards'' \u2013 Shreya Ghoshal\n* ''Vijay Music awards'' \u2013 ''[[Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa (soundtrack)|Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa]]''\n\n; [[Vijay Awards]]<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.tamilkey.com/winners-list-of-vijay-awards-2011.html|title=Winners List Of Vijay Awards 2011|publisher=tamilkey.com|date=26 June 2011|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Vijay Award for Best Music Director|Best Music Director]] \u2013 A. R. Rahman\n* [[Vijay Award for Best Male Playback Singer|Best Male Playback Singer]] \u2013 Vijay Prakash\n* [[Vijay Award for Best Female Playback Singer|Best Female Playback Singer]] \u2013 Shreya Ghoshal\n* [[Vijay Award for Favourite Heroine|Favorite Heroine]] \u2013 Trisha Krishnan\n\n; [[Filmfare Awards South]]\n* \n* [[Filmfare Best Music Director Award (Tamil)|Best Music Director]] \u2013 A. R. Rahman\n* [[Filmfare Best Lyricist Award (Tamil)|Best Lyricist]] \u2013 [[Thamarai]] (for \"Mannipaaya\")\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Cinematographer|Best Cinematographer]] \u2013 [[Manoj Paramahamsa]]\n\n==Sequel==\nIn February 2018, [[Gautham Menon]] announced a sequel to the film, titled ''[[Ondraga]]''. This film will be a [[road movie]] - [[hyperlink cinema|hyperlink film]] which will focus on Karthik and his best friends from college travelling to the [[United States]] to attend a wedding ten years after the events of the first film. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://scroll.in/reel/869484/gautham-menon-and-r-madhavan-team-up-for-vinnaithaandi-varuvaayaa-sequel |title=Gautham Menon and R Madhavan team up for 'Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa' sequel |date=21 February 2018 |work=Scroll.in}}</ref> Initially, Menon had stated [[R. Madhavan]] would be playing the role of an older Karthik. After Madhavan dropped out of the project, Silambarasan agreed to reprise the role he originally played. [[Trisha]] and [[Samantha Akkineni]] will also be reprising their roles from the first film. [[Tovino Thomas]] and  [[Puneeth Rajkumar]] will be playing the roles as Karthik's [[Malayalam]] and [[Kannada]] friends respectively. Telugu actors [[Allu Arjun]], [[Nani]], [[Sai Dharam Tej]], [[Varun Tej]] and [[Vijay Deverakonda]] have been approached to play the role of Karthik's [[Telugu people|Telugu]] friend. Actresses [[Tamannaah]] and [[Anushka Shetty]] are being considered as a third female lead. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://regional.pinkvilla.com/tamil/news/gautham-menons-multi-lingual-film-feature-anushka-shetty-tamannah-puneeth-rajkumar/|title=Gautham Menon's multi-lingual film to feature Anushka Shetty, Tamannaah and Puneeth Rajkumar|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://amp.ibtimes.co.in/madhavan-replaces-simbu-gautham-menons-ondraga-761404|title=Madhavan replaces Simbu in Gautham Menon's Ondraga|first=Shekhar H|last=Hooli|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==In popular culture==\nThe dialogue \"Inga Enna Solludhu\" spoken by VTV Ganesh inspired a 2014 film of [[Inga Enna Solluthu|same name]] which was produced and acted by Ganesh.<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Kollywood-movie-titles-based-on-popular-dialogues/articleshow/20831436.cms</ref> The scenes and dialogues were parodied in ''[[Tamizh Padam 2]]'' (2018).<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/tamizh-padam-2/tamizh-padam-2-review.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|1609168}}\n\n{{Gautham Menon}}\n\n[[Category:Films shot in Goa]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Malta]]\n[[Category:2010s multilingual films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s romance films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Kerala]]\n[[Category:Films set in Chennai]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Gautham Menon]]\n[[Category:Indian interfaith romance films]]\n[[Category:2010 films]]\n[[Category:Tamil films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Films shot in New York City]]\n[[Category:Indian films set in New York City]]\n[[Category:2010s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by A. R. Rahman]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian multilingual films]]\n[[Category:Indian coming-of-age films]]\n[[Category:Films about filmmaking]]\n[[Category:Films about film directors and producers]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2010 film by Gautham Menon}}\n{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya\n| image          = Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Gautham Menon]]\n| producer       = [[Escape Artists Motion Pictures|P. Madan]]<br />[[VTV Ganesh]]<br />[[Elred Kumar]]<br />Jayaraman\n| writer         = [[Gautham Menon]]\n| starring       = [[Silambarasan]]<br />[[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]]\n| narrator       = [[Silambarasan]]\n| music          = [[A. R. Rahman]]\n| cinematography = [[Manoj Paramahamsa]]\n| editing        = [[Anthony (film editor)|Anthony Gonsalves]]\n| studio         = [[Escape Artists Motion Pictures]]<br />[[RS Infotainment]]\n| distributor    = [[Udhayanidhi Stalin|Red Giant Movies]]<br/>Two95 Entertainment\n| released       = {{Film date|df=y|2010|02|26}}\n| runtime        = 167 minutes\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = Tamil\n}}\n'''''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa''''' ({{Literal translation|Will you cross the skies for me?}}) is a 2010 Indian Tamil-language [[romantic drama]] film directed and written by [[Gautham Menon]], featuring [[Silambarasan]] and [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]] in the lead roles. The film, distributed by [[Udhayanidhi Stalin]], features [[Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa (soundtrack)|soundtrack]] composed by [[A. R. Rahman]], cinematography by [[Manoj Paramahamsa]] and editing by [[Anthony (film editor)|Anthony Gonsalves]]. The story was simultaneously shot in [[Cinema of Andhra Pradesh|Telugu]] as ''[[Ye Maaya Chesave]]'', starring [[Naga Chaitanya]] and [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu]], however, with a different cast and climax.<ref name=\"remake\">{{cite news|author=Daithota, Madhu|title='I don't treat Naga Chaitanya like a star kid'|work=Times of India|accessdate=14 September 2009 |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/news-interviews/I-dont-treat-Naga-Chaitanya-like-a-star-kid/articleshow/5005397.cms|date=14 September 2009}}</ref>\n\nLaunched after a wave of publicity posters with no details about the cast and crew, ''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'' began its first schedule of filming in February 2009.<ref name=\"mystery\">{{cite web|year=2009|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya \u2013 The Silambarasan mystery unveiled|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=13 February 2009|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-09-02/vinnaithaandi-varuvaaya-13-02-09.html}}</ref> Shooting continued through 2009, with the film garnering significant media interest, through schedules in Malta and the United States.<ref name=\"malta\">{{cite web|author=Moviebuzz|year=2009|title=Simbu and Trisha go to Malta|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=12 May 2009|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14887420}}</ref> Before release, it became the first Tamil project to have a music soundtrack premiere outside of India, with a successful launch at the [[British Academy of Film and Television Arts]] (BAFTAs) in London.<ref name=\"abroadmusic\">{{cite web|year=2009|title=Silambarasan, Trisha, Gautam & Rahman in London! |publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=21 December 2009|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/dec-09-04/silambarasan-trisha-vinnaithaandi-varuvaaya-21-12-09.html}}</ref>\n\n''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'' explores the complicated relationship between a [[Hindu]] [[Tamils|Tamil]] boy, Karthik Sivakumar, and a [[Malayali]] [[Christianity|Christian]] girl, Jessie Thekekuttu from [[Alappuzha]], [[Kerala]]. Karthik falls in love with Jessie only to be met by her indifference and reluctance as they belong to different religions and her strict conservative family will never consent to their union. The film released on 26 February 2010, along with the Telugu version to advance bookings worldwide.<ref name=\"rediff1\">{{cite web|publisher=[[Rediff]]|url=http://movies.rediff.com/slide-show/2010/jun/23/slide-show-1-south-half-year-report-of-tamil-cinema.htm|title=Half-yearly BO report: Suriya rules Tamil|date=23 June 2010|accessdate=23 June 2010}}</ref><ref name=\"behindwoods.com\">{{citation|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies-slide-shows/movie-4/box-office-2010/vinnaithaandi-varuvaayaa.html|title=Box Office 2010|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref> Upon release, it achieved highly positive reviews, with several critics giving \"modern classic\" status, whilst also becoming a commercially successful venture.<ref name=\"rediffreview\">{{cite web|author=Srinivasan, Pavithra|year=2010|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa is a must watch|publisher=[[Rediff]]|accessdate=26 February 2010|url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/feb/26/review-vinnaithaandi-varuvaayaa.htm}}</ref><ref name=\"sifyreview\">{{cite web|publisher=[[Sify]]|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya review|accessdate=26 February 2010|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/review.php?id=14933091&ctid=5&cid=2429}}</ref> It was later remade in [[Bollywood|Hindi]] as ''[[Ekk Deewana Tha]]'' starring [[Prateik Babbar]] and [[Amy Jackson]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Maybe I got the casting wrong: Gautham Menon|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-02-28/news-interviews/31107562_1_amy-jackson-gautham-menon-ekk-deewana-tha|accessdate=11 May 2012|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=28 February 2012|author=Sunayana Suresh}}</ref> in 2012. After the 7 years, [[Gautham Menon]] officially announced, that a filming of a sequel would begin soon with new four actors and Silambarasan.\n\n==Plot==\n\nKarthik ([[Silambarasan]]) is a [[Mechanical Engineering]] graduate in [[Chennai]] who aspires to become a filmmaker. His friend introduces him to cinematographer Ganesh ([[Ganesh Janardhanan]]). With Ganesh's help Karthik becomes an assistant to director [[K. S. Ravikumar]]. Karthik's family, who are [[Tamil people|Tamil]] Hindu's, rent Jessie's ([[Trisha Krishnan]]) house. Jessie is from a conservative [[Malayali people|Malayali]] [[Saint Thomas Christians|Nasrani Christian]]/Syrian Catholic family from [[Alappuzha]], [[Kerala]], that lives upstairs.<ref name=\"manorama\">{{cite web|publisher=[[Malayala Manorama|Metro Manorama Kochi]]|title=Marunadan Cinemayile Malayali|accessdate=1 November 2014|url=http://epaper.manoramaonline.com/edaily/FlashClient/Show_Story_IPad.aspx?storySrc=aHR0cDovL2VwYXBlci5tYW5vcmFtYW9ubGluZS5jb20vTU1EYWlseS9Lb2NoaS8yMDE0LzExLzAxL0YvTU1EYWlseV9Lb2NoaV8yMDE0XzExXzAxX0ZfTVRfMDI2X1BSLmpwZw==&uname=&ipad=N}}</ref> Karthik falls in love with Jessie the moment he meets her. Karthik tries to interact with Jessie, who is afraid of speaking to men around her strict father, and ends up angering her. Unable to hide his feelings any longer, Karthik confesses his love for her; she does not respond. A few days later, Karthik learns from his sister that Jessie has gone to Kerala to visit her grandmother. He and Ganesh end up in Kerala to look for her. After several days, he finds her and apologises. She introduces him to her family in Kerala as her \"classmate\". Jessie denies she has any feelings for him but agrees to be his friend. On the train journey back home, however, the two get close and share a kiss. Karthik is convinced Jessie loves him; the two meet several times and Jessie begins to admit that she also likes Karthik, but wants to refrain from any problems because she knows her father wouldn't give her hand in marriage to a Hindu. Consequently, due to various misunderstandings between Jessie's brother and Karthik, her parents learn of their supposed affair. They fix a match and schedule her wedding. The day arrives and midway through the ceremony, Jessie refuses to marry the groom, displeasing everyone in her family. Karthik, who had, without anyone's knowledge, come to Kerala to witness the wedding is ecstatic and secretly visits Jessie at her home. It is then that Jessie admits she has indeed fallen in love with him. Karthik and Jessie continue to love each other without the knowledge of their parents.\n\nAt this point of time, Karthik goes to [[Goa]] on a 45-day shoot, where he gets rather busy. Meanwhile, the topic of Jessie's marriage comes up again at her home when the guy whom she refused to marry earlier pays them a visit. Panicking, Jessie calls Karthik and tells him that she wants to elope with him. Karthik, since he is travelling through less than ideal places, tells Jessie to stay in Chennai for now, and that soon he would be back and they can discuss. Jessie stops taking Karthik's calls and so he goes back one night to check on Jessie. He comes to know that Jessie has decided to break up, as the relationship is not peaceful due to her parents' disapproval. She says she has agreed to marry a boy of their choice. When Karthik pleads her not to do it, she tells him that a time had come when she was willing to elope, but the moment was gone. She doesn't want Karthik to wait for her too long, as he has his dreams to fulfill. Karthik later comes to know that she is married and settled abroad in UK.\n\nTwo years later, Karthik meets Nandini ([[Samantha Ruth Prabhu]]). She falls in love with him, but is rejected by Karthik by saying that he hasn't yet gotten over Jessie. He then comes up with a script for his first film, which happens to be his very own love story. He calls upon [[Naga Chaitanya|Naga Chaitanya Akkineni]] as the film's protagonist, Nandini as the female lead and Ganesh as the film's cinematographer, and the film is eventually titled ''Jessie''. While shooting for the film in New York, he sees Jessie and she comes to speak with him. She admits that she is not married and is still in love with him, and he too says she is still in his heart. Karthik proposes yet again and they get married the same day. This is actually revealed to be the end scene in Karthik's movie \u2013 which Karthik and Jessie in real life are watching together in the theatre. After it gets over, it is revealed to the audience that Jessie had in fact seen Karthik in New York but had not come forward to meet him. She is married now and hence asks Karthik to move on. She tells Karthik that they cannot lead a life which is full of obstacles and they part, once and for all to lead different lives and different destinies.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n* [[Silambarasan|Simbu]] as Karthik Sivakumar, a [[Tamil people|Tamil]] [[Hindu]].<ref name=\"manorama\"/>\n* [[Trisha Krishnan|Trisha]] as Jessie Thekekuttu, a [[Saint Thomas Christians|Syrian Christian]] Syrian Catholic [[Malayali]] girl.<ref name=\"manorama\"/>\n* [[VTV Ganesh]] as Ganesh, a [[cinematographer]]\n* [[Babu Antony]] as Joseph Thekekuttu\n* [[Kitty (actor)|Kitty]] as Sivakumar\n* [[Uma Padmanabhan]] as Mrs. Sivakumar\n* Arjuna as Jerry Thekekuttu\n* [[Lakshmi Ramakrishnan]] as Teresa Thekekuttu\n* Trisha Alex as Karthik's sister\n* [[K. S. Ravikumar]] as a [[Film director|Director]]\n* [[Pradeep Kottayam]] as George, Jessie's uncle in Kerala.\n* [[Janani Iyer]] as an [[assistant director]] to K. S. Ravikumar.\n* [[Lena (actress)|Lena]] as Rita's mother\n* [[Sudheesh]] as Praveen\n* [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu]] in a cameo appearance as the [[actress]] Nandini\n* [[Naga Chaitanya]] in a cameo appearance as himself\n{{colend}}\n\n==Production==\nAfter making a series of action films, Gautham Menon actively chose to make an \"out and out love story\" at the insistence of his close associates, and marked a return to genre for the first time since ''[[Minnale]]'' (2001). Initially titled ''Vennilavae Vennillavae'', he started writing the film as a simple love story which slowly became an intense love story, as the scripting phase progressed. Stating that the film would narrate the romantic tale of two people called Karthik and Jessie over a period of almost three years, he revealed that the film would be \"conversation driven\" and hoped \"everybody will identify with the lead pair\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/tamil/interview.php?cid=2408&id=14932884|title=Welcome to Sify.com|website=www.sify.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> Menon took the script to producer [[Manjula Ghattamaneni]], who asked him to narrate the film to her brother [[Mahesh Babu]] and the movie was a [[Tamil language|Tamil]] and [[Telugu language|Telugu]] bilingual. Menon initially felt that the film would not suit the actor, but later agreed preliminary terms to make it in Telugu titled ''Jessie'' with the actor and have [[A. R. Rahman]] as the music composer, as he was impressed with the story.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/features/Interviews/interview-5/director/gautham-menon-2.html|title=Director Gautham Vasudev Menon - Interview - Behindwoods.com - Vaaranam Aayiram Kakka Kakka Pachaikili Muthucharam Minnale Suriya Kamal Haasan Kamal Hassan images tamil picture gallery images|website=www.behindwoods.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nContinuing from the earlier proposed theme of ''Vennilavae Vennillavae'', Menon later chose to use the second line of the song to title his film as ''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'', after it was suggested by the cinematographer [[Manoj Paramahamsa]].<ref name=\"rediff\">{{cite web|url=http://specials.rediff.com/movies/2009/mar/02slde1-gautam-menons-vinnaithandi-varuvaya.htm|title=rediff.com: Gautam Menon's new love story|website=specials.rediff.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> Menon discussed a Tamil and Telugu version of the script with several actors including [[Dhanush]] and [[Allu Arjun]] who had wanted changes to be made to the climax, and described being \"one week away\" from starting the project with a debutant actor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-simbu-is-classy-i-m-local-dhanush-tells-gautham-menon-2206388|title='Simbu is classy, I'm local', Dhanush tells Gautham Menon|date=26 April 2016|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2011/02/12/between-reviews-shooting-from-the-lip/|title=Between Reviews: Shooting from the Lip|date=12 February 2011|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewsminute.com/article/dhanush-chameleon-simbu-has-too-many-distractions-gautham-menon-interview-53004?amp|title=Dhanush is a chameleon, Simbu has too many distractions: Gautham Menon interview|date=17 November 2016|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> But In late January 2009, Menon confirmed that he was in discussions with [[Silambarasan]] and [[Trisha (actress)|Trisha]] to portray the lead roles from the script. After finding out that Silambarasan had dates available as a result of the delay in the shoot of [[Vignesh Shivan]]'s ''[[Podaa Podi]]'' (2012), Menon chose to halt the production of his ongoing ''Chennaiyil Oru Mazhaikaalam'' and finalise pre-production work on ''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa''. Menon added that Silambarasan was \"apt for this kind of a film\" and was \"ready to experiment and try something different\" from his usual film roles, prompting him to agree to star in the film.<ref name=\"rediff\"/> As Menon was working with Trisha on ''Chennaiyil Oru Mazhaikaalam'', he chose to use her dates for ''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'' instead.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/exclusive-gautham-to-start-a-quickie-with-simbu-news-tamil-kkfsxQebaiesi.html|title=Exclusive: Gautham to start a quickie with Simbu!|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> To pique interest before the official announcement, the makers released a series of film posters featuring Silambarasan and Trisha inspired from previous classic Tamil films. The team used posters inspired from ''[[Geethanjali (1989 film)|Geethanjali]]'' (1989), ''[[Minsara Kanavu]]'' (1997), ''[[Dil Se]]'' (1998), ''[[Alaipayuthey]]'' (2000) and ''[[Kaakha Kaakha]]'' (2003). Other members of the technical crew included Menon's regular collaborators editor [[Anthony (film editor)|Anthony]], art director [[Rajeevan]], costume designer Nalini Sriram and lyricist [[Thamarai]]. The project was jointly produced by [[Escape Artists Motion Pictures]] and [[RS Infotainment]], with [[Elred Kumar]], [[VTV Ganesh|Ganesh]], Madhan and Jayaraman as producers.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-09-03/vinnaithandi-varuvaaya-16-02-09.html|title=A.R. Rahman to compose for Silambarasan's flick - Behindwoods.com - Tamil Movie News - Vinnaithaandi Varuvaya Silambarasan Trisha Gautham Vasudev Menon A.R. Rahman|website=www.behindwoods.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/feb-09-02/vinnaithaandi-varuvaaya-13-02-09.html|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya - The Silambarasan mystery unveiled - Behindwoods.com - Tamil Movies News - Gautham Menon Trisha A.R. Rahman|website=www.behindwoods.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nFor the role of a mentor to Karthik's character, Menon first approached [[Vivek (actor)|Vivek]], but he turned down the opportunity. Later, one of the film's producers, [[VTV Ganesh|Ganesh]], was cast in the role, in what later became his breakthrough film as an actor.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vm8100Ii8Q4|title=\"Those who know me refer to me as Jessie.\" - One Film One Facet - Gautham Menon|last=Film Companion South|date=20 February 2018|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref> Chennai-based model [[Janani Iyer]] was recruited to portray the role of an assistant director who falls in love with Karthik, but the role was later reshot with [[Samantha Ruth Prabhu|Samantha]], who worked as the lead actress of the film's Telugu version. Janani Iyer was subsequently seen in the background of several scenes where Karthik is shown to be a part of a film production team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/did-you-know|title=Did You Know - Movies - Tamil - Entertainment - The Times of India|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> [[Ashwin Kakumanu]] also auditioned for the role of Jessy's brother in the film and was selected, but eventually did not feature after having a clash of dates.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-actors/ashwin-kakumanu/ashwin-kakumanu-interview.html|title=Ashwin Kakumanu Interview|website=www.behindwoods.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8v6O260NDhE|title=How Gautham Menon Explained a Lip-Lock Scene? - What Happened? - Ashwin Explains - US 56|last=BehindwoodsTV|date=13 July 2017|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018|via=YouTube}}</ref>\n\n===Filming===\nScenes were shot in the lakes of [[Alappuzha]] during April 2009 for a month, with the [[houseboat]]s doubling up as caravans.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/malayalam-film-not-now-says-trisha-news-tamil-kkfsjEbcighsi.html|title=Malayalam film? Not now, says Trisha|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn May, the team moved to [[Malta]] to film the song sequences for \"Hosanna\" and \"Omana Penne\", choreographed by Flexy Stu.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/simbu-and-trisha-go-to-malta-news-tamil-kkfrXGhhjdasi.html|title=Simbu and Trisha go to Malta|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref> For the particular song sequences in the film, Menon wanted \"churches, water and caves\" and convinced the producers to finance a trip to Malta, and in the process, the team became the first South Indian film to shoot in the country. Scenes were shot in places including [[Valletta]], [[Mdina]], [[Gozo]] and [[Comino]], as well as in lanes, alleys, eight churches and during the time of a village feast. The makers brought along a crew of twenty-six people to Malta, with ten local workers also helping on the production. The shoot lasted ten days and cost approximately \u20ac90,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20090528/local/bollywood-director-discovers-malta.258682|title=Bollywood director discovers Malta|first=Allied Newspapers|last=Ltd|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.com.mt/articles/2009-07-18/news/tamil-film-partly-shot-in-malta-nearing-completion-227946/|title=Tamil Film partly shot in Malta nearing completion - The Malta Independent|website=www.independent.com.mt|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2009, the team flew to the [[United States]] to complete the final filming schedule. Scenes were shot throughout locations in [[Manhattan]] and [[New Jersey]], with particular shots filmed at [[Brooklyn Bridge]], [[Central Park]] and [[Times Square]].\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/simbu-trisha-off-to-new-york-news-tamil-kkfrvXefdaasi.html|title=Simbu & Trisha off to New York|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-news-1/oct-09-03/vinnaithandi-varuvaya-16-10-09.html|title=Silambarasan and Trisha celebrating Deepavali in NY - Tamil Movie News - Vinnaithandi Varuvaya - Silambarasan - Gautham Menon - Trisha - Behindwoods.com|website=www.behindwoods.com|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe film was given a \"U/A\" certificate by the [[Central Board of Film Certification|Indian Film Certification Board]] as they believed \"the love in the film was too intense for a child to understand\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://silverscreen.in/tamil/features/gautham-menon-interview-on-movies-music-romance/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170216081053/https://silverscreen.in/tamil/features/gautham-menon-interview-on-movies-music-romance/|title=Gautham Menon Interview: On Movies, Music & Romance|archivedate=16 February 2017|work=Silverscreen.in|accessdate=16 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Critical reception===\nThe film opened to highly positive reviews from critics. ''[[Oneindia.in]]'' said \"The slow phase of the second half and frequent use of bad words (Chennai Tamil) are major minuses in Gautham's narration. But these are all not preventing one to enjoy the content of true and painful love of the film!\"<ref>{{citation|url=http://entertainment.oneindia.in/tamil/reviews/2010/vinnaithandi-varuvaya-review-270210.html|title=Vinnaithandi Varuvaya \u2013 Review|publisher=oneindia.in|date=27 February 2010|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n''[[Sify]]'' said that it was \"Very good\" further citing \"The film is a must watch for those who cares for cinema of sense and substance. It stresses the fact that Tamil cinema has to break the mould if it aims to grab eyeballs. Gautham Menon has crafted a movie that will stay in our hearts for a long, long time.\"<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.sify.com/movies/vinnaithaandi-varuvaaya-review-review-tamil-14933091.html|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya review|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref> ''Indiaglitz'' stated \"If and only if, you have all the time in the world, and you like the slow romantic genre, you'll enjoy this one.\"<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/review/10901.html|title=innaithandi Varuvaya Movie Review|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=26 February 2010 |accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nPavithra Srinivasan of ''[[Rediff.com]]'' called the film a \"Must watch\" further citing \"The best part about VTV is that it revolves around people, rather than events. It's like putting a camera into the intimate, everyday life of two people and following them on their adventures. The characters go through a whirlwind of emotions, laugh and cry, and take you along with them.\" However, the reviewer points out certain drawbacks in the film citing \"On the minus side, VTV suffers from the same defect as Vaaranam Aayiram: the second half lags in pace. The dialogues and confrontations are repetitive. There's a would-be love-track that seems unnecessary before the story takes off again.\"<ref>{{citation|url=http://movies.rediff.com/report/2010/feb/26/review-vinnaithaandi-varuvaayaa.htm|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa is a must watch|publisher=[[Rediff.com]]|date=26 February 2010|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nMalathi Rangarajan from ''[[The Hindu]]'' said \"Twenty two-year old Karthik's true-to-life overtures, reactions and recklessness are just as you would expect from a director of Menon's calibre. It is his authentic depiction of Jessie's confusion that's all the more amazing \u2013 Menon's complete understanding of a woman's psyche bowls you over! So do the young lovers!\"<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.hindu.com/cp/2010/03/05/stories/2010030550040200.htm|title=Taste of candyfloss \u2013 Vinnai Thaandi Varuvaaya|work=The Hindu|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref> Aravindan D. I. of ''nowrunning.com'' gave the film three stars out of five and said \"Gautam Vasudev Menon's \"Vinnaithaandi Varuvaaya\" is a clean romantic story without any deviation or sub-plots.\"<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.nowrunning.com/movie/6351/tamil/vinnaithaandi-varuvaayaa/2498/review.htm|title=Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa Review|publisher=nowrunning.com|date=27 February 2010|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n''Chennai Online'' said, ''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'' (VTV) is an excellent effort on the part of Gautam Vasudev Menon in narrating a clean romantic story without any deviation from the plot\" and further cited \"As is Menon\u2019s forte, the dialogues and the execution of scenes are top-notch. The joys of falling of love and the pangs of separation have been portrayed well. The way Simbu nurtures his love for Jesse and the positive but ambiguous reactions from Trisha to his overtures are very nice indeed.\"<ref>{{citation|url=http://chennaionline.com/movies/moviereviews/20101227121207/Movie-Review-Vinnai-Thaandi-Varuvaaya.col|title=Movie Review: Vinnai Thaandi Varuvaaya|publisher=chennaionline.com|date=27 February 2010|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\nRaman Nalluswamy Thevar, an Indian author wrote an [[E-book|e-Book]] titled \"One Awesome Girl\"  which narrates the dialogue \"One-way ticket to Heart-break city\" delivered by Simbu. Raman stated that his debut contains his auto-biography and semi-biography which received positive reviews.\n\n===Box office===\n''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'' took a grand opening, grossing around {{INRConvert|9.7|m}} in its first three days in Chennai.<ref>{{citation|url=http://sify.com/movies/tamil/fullstory.php?id=14933568&cid=13525926|title=CBO \u2013 Feb 26 to 28|date=2 March 2010|publisher=[[Sify]]|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref> The film grossed {{INRConvert|157.5|m}} at the Chennai box office in the 12th weekend. It totally grossed {{INRConvert|500|m}} and was officially declared a blockbuster.<ref name=\"behindwoods.com\"/>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{main|Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa (soundtrack)}}\nThe soundtrack was composed by [[A. R. Rahman]]. ''Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa'' marked the beginning of a collaboration between Rahman, Silambarasan and [[Gautham Menon]].<ref>{{cite news|first=M|last=Suganth|title=2 crore for NEP audio rights!|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-05-10/news-interviews/31642728_1_audio-industry-ilaiyaraaja-audio-rights|accessdate=3 October 2012|newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|date=10 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe world premiere was held at [[BAFTA]] in London on 18 December 2009 and later it was relaunched in [[Chennai]] on 20 January 2010. The album consists of seven tracks.<ref>{{cite web\n|url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/slide-show/slide-show-south-top-tamil-films-of-2010/20101209.htm |title=Top Tamil films of 2010\n|publisher=[[Rediff]]|accessdate=9 December 2009}}</ref> The audio received good pre-release response and was marked as No. 1 in Asia, in advance bookings.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sify.com/movies/Vinnai-Thandi-Varuvaaya-audio-creates-history-imagegallery-kollywood-kbjmXAjfdfd.html|title=Vinnai Thandi Varuvaaya audio creates history!|publisher=[[Sify]]}}</ref> The album was ranked among the best musicals of 2010.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/62922.html|title=REWIND: The Music of 2010|publisher=IndiaGlitz|date=7 January 2011|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Accolades==\n; [[Edison Awards (India)|Edison Awards]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kollytalk.com/cinenews/simbu-and-trisha-win-edison-awards-for-excellence-in-cinema/|title=Simbu and Trisha win Edison awards 2011, for Vinnai Thaandi Varuvaaya|date=15 February 2011|accessdate=17 February 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110622073416/http://www.kollytalk.com/cinenews/simbu-and-trisha-win-edison-awards-for-excellence-in-cinema/|archive-date=22 June 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n* Best Actor \u2013 [[Silambarasan Rajendar]]\n* Best Actress \u2013 [[Trisha Krishnan]]\n* Best Male Singer \u2013 [[Vijay Prakash]]\n\n; Vikatan Awards<ref>{{cite news|url=http://kollywoodz.com/exclusive-results-of-ananda-vikatan-awards-2010/|title=Exclusive: Results of Ananda Vikatan Awards 2010|publisher=Kollywoodz}}</ref>\n* Best Music Director \u2013 [[A. R. Rahman]]\n* Best Male Singer \u2013 [[Benny Dayal]]\n* Best Female Singer \u2013 [[Shreya Ghoshal]]\n* Best Lyricist \u2013 [[Thamarai]]\n* Best Costume Designer \u2013 Nalini Sriram<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kollywoodz.com/exclusive-results-of-ananda-vikatan-awards-2010/ |title=Exclusive: Results of Ananda Vikatan Awards 2010 |publisher=Kollywoodz.com |date=22 January 2011 |accessdate=17 January 2012}}</ref>\n\n;BIG Tamil Entertainment Awards<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movie-articles/movies-08/big-awards-28-03-11.html|title=A 'big' night for Tamil entertainment industry|publisher=Behindwoods|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n* Most Entertaining Actor \u2013 Silambarasan Rajendar\n* Most Entertaining Male Singer \u2013 Vijay Prakash\n\n; [[Vijay Music Awards]]\n\n* ''Vijay Music awards'' \u2013 A. R. Rahman\n* ''Vijay Music awards'' \u2013 Vijay Prakash\n* ''Vijay Music awards'' \u2013 Shreya Ghoshal\n* ''Vijay Music awards'' \u2013 ''[[Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa (soundtrack)|Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa]]''\n\n; [[Vijay Awards]]<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.tamilkey.com/winners-list-of-vijay-awards-2011.html|title=Winners List Of Vijay Awards 2011|publisher=tamilkey.com|date=26 June 2011|accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Vijay Award for Best Music Director|Best Music Director]] \u2013 A. R. Rahman\n* [[Vijay Award for Best Male Playback Singer|Best Male Playback Singer]] \u2013 Vijay Prakash\n* [[Vijay Award for Best Female Playback Singer|Best Female Playback Singer]] \u2013 Shreya Ghoshal\n* [[Vijay Award for Favourite Heroine|Favorite Heroine]] \u2013 Trisha Krishnan\n\n; [[Filmfare Awards South]]\n* \n* [[Filmfare Best Music Director Award (Tamil)|Best Music Director]] \u2013 A. R. Rahman\n* [[Filmfare Best Lyricist Award (Tamil)|Best Lyricist]] \u2013 [[Thamarai]] (for \"Mannipaaya\")\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Cinematographer|Best Cinematographer]] \u2013 [[Manoj Paramahamsa]]\n\n==Sequel==\nIn February 2018, [[Gautham Menon]] announced a sequel to the film, titled ''[[Ondraga]]''. This film will be a [[road movie]] - [[hyperlink cinema|hyperlink film]] which will focus on Karthik and his best friends from college travelling to the [[United States]] to attend a wedding ten years after the events of the first film. <ref>{{cite news|url=https://scroll.in/reel/869484/gautham-menon-and-r-madhavan-team-up-for-vinnaithaandi-varuvaayaa-sequel |title=Gautham Menon and R Madhavan team up for 'Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa' sequel |date=21 February 2018 |work=Scroll.in}}</ref> Initially, Menon had stated [[R. Madhavan]] would be playing the role of an older Karthik. After Madhavan dropped out of the project, Silambarasan agreed to reprise the role he originally played. [[Trisha]] and [[Samantha Akkineni]] will also be reprising their roles from the first film. [[Tovino Thomas]] and  [[Puneeth Rajkumar]] will be playing the roles as Karthik's [[Malayalam]] and [[Kannada]] friends respectively. Telugu actors [[Allu Arjun]], [[Nani]], [[Sai Dharam Tej]], [[Varun Tej]] and [[Vijay Deverakonda]] have been approached to play the role of Karthik's [[Telugu people|Telugu]] friend. Actresses [[Tamannaah]] and [[Anushka Shetty]] are being considered as a third female lead. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://regional.pinkvilla.com/tamil/news/gautham-menons-multi-lingual-film-feature-anushka-shetty-tamannah-puneeth-rajkumar/|title=Gautham Menon's multi-lingual film to feature Anushka Shetty, Tamannaah and Puneeth Rajkumar|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://amp.ibtimes.co.in/madhavan-replaces-simbu-gautham-menons-ondraga-761404|title=Madhavan replaces Simbu in Gautham Menon's Ondraga|first=Shekhar H|last=Hooli|publisher=|accessdate=19 September 2018}}</ref>\n\n==In popular culture==\nThe dialogue \"Inga Enna Solludhu\" spoken by VTV Ganesh inspired a 2014 film of [[Inga Enna Solluthu|same name]] which was produced and acted by Ganesh.<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/movies/news/Kollywood-movie-titles-based-on-popular-dialogues/articleshow/20831436.cms</ref> The scenes and dialogues were parodied in ''[[Tamizh Padam 2]]'' (2018).<ref>http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/tamizh-padam-2/tamizh-padam-2-review.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|1609168}}\n\n{{Gautham Menon}}\n\n[[Category:Films shot in Goa]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Malta]]\n[[Category:2010s multilingual films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s romance films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Kerala]]\n[[Category:Films set in Chennai]]\n